          "reviewTitle": "Good Coverage, Nice Finish",
          "reviewText": "I recently tried this foundation, and it has quickly become one of my favorites. I have oily skin, and finding a foundation that stays put without breaking down throughout the day can be a challenge, but this one performs beautifully. The texture is lightweight yet provides buildable coverage, allowing me to achieve both a natural everyday look or a fuller coverage finish. One of the things I appreciate most is how it controls shine without feeling heavy or cakey. Even after several hours of wear, my skin still looks fresh and smooth. Another major plus is that it doesn\u2019t oxidize. The shade I apply in the morning stays true all day long, which is rare in many foundations I\u2019ve used before. It also blurs pores nicely and gives a soft, semi-matte finish that feels comfortable and breathable. Overall, this foundation is a great pick for anyone with oily or combination skin who wants long-lasting coverage without worrying about color changes or excessive shine. I\u2019d highly recommend it if you\u2019re looking for a dependable, everyday foundation that performs well under different conditions. Pros: Controls oil and shine effectively Lightweight, buildable coverage Does not oxidize Long-lasting and comfortable wear Smooths and blurs pores Cons: Might require a primer for very long days if you have extremely oily skin Perfect for anyone looking for a reliable foundation that stays true and fresh all day!",
